[ctns_make id='gen_axioms_field_axioms_closure_under_addition']

  [ctns_front style='']
Field Axioms<br/><br/>Closure Under Addition
  [/ctns_front]  

  [ctns_back style='width:80%;']
A set $$\mathbb{F}$$ is <strong>closed under addition</strong> for all values $$x, y \in \mathbb{F}$$ <br/><br/>if $$x+y \in \mathbb{F}$$ and $$x+y$$ is unique.
  [/ctns_back]  

  [ctns_frontspeak]
Field Axioms -- -- Closure Under Addition
  [/ctns_frontspeak]  

  [ctns_backspeak]
A set F is closed under addition for all values x and y in F if the sum of x plus y is both unique and a member of F
  [/ctns_backspeak]  

[/ctns_make]
